                                                                                                </div>
                        

                        <p>“When the IGSP first started, there were not many people or researchers on campus that used genomic technologies,” Wray said. “We have succeeded, and that’s become well integrated into the University infrastructure.”</p>
<p>Willard noted that the IGSP will now be focusing more on biological and medical aspects of genomics.</p>
<p>“It’s not all about the technology,” he said. “It’s more about how one uses genomic information to address questions of life science and medicine.” </p>
